<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The function parameter argv is declared as char *const *argv, so argv[0] has type char * (pointer to non-const char). The code only reads argv[0] (compares to NULL and passes it to strrchr/strlen/strcpy), so the pointed-to characters could and should be const-qualified. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. A suitable fix is to declare the parameter as const char *const *argv (or at least const char *argv[]), e.g. static void set_self_name(int argc, const char *const *argv).
</scenario>
